folder: Central Park West & 69th Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Central Park West, west side, from 69th to 71st Streets. At the left on the N.W. corner of 69th Street is the clearing resulting from the demolition of two buildings. The white building with Corinthian columns in the centre is the Portuguese synagogue Congregation Shearith Israel.

October 20, 1926.

P.L. Sperr, Photographer.

NEG # 4781
title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 69th Street

folder: Central Park West & 69th Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1)
Central Park West at the N.W. corner of 69th Street, showing
start of demolition work on buildings.
At the right may be seen a portion of the Portuguese synagogue
Congregation Shearith Israel.
September 9, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, showing the corner building in the process of demolition.
October 30, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)
The same, showing clearing after demolition of building shown in No. 1.
October 20, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
